<subSubSection id="8B60628AFE577BAE9447C18EE9E35FA5" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="BEFA84709507995B30C5110CD971896D" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="908C60797D1807580C215804A26AC8DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
A worldwide temperate species found in a wide variety of habitats, but most often on damp shaded soil or fallen logs and tree stumps. Its distribution in Chile remains poorly understood but it is common in the more temperate southern regions such as 
<normalizedToken id="FB6015D179374246AB809DE559DFF5F6" originalValue="Bío">Bio</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="F1362B1378997CE90A49F6A868E7F8CF" originalValue="Bío">Bio</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="39EAA10B3DB2B418B7CA0A127BF7B46E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.77.10926" author="Ireland, RR" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 20" refId="B7" refString="Ireland, RR, Bellolio, IG, Larrain, J, Rodriguez, R, 2017. Studies on the moss flora of the Bio-Bio Region of Chile: Part 3. PhytoKeys 77: 1 - 20, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.77.10926" title="Studies on the moss flora of the Bio-Bio Region of Chile: Part 3." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.77.10926" volume="77" year="2017">Ireland et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). It is characterized by dioicous sexual condition, rosulate stems, small obovate leaves that are spirally twisted around the stem when dry, a costa excurrent into a medium to long awn, moderately well-developed limbidium, serrate distal leaf margins, and small brown rhizoidal tubers (Illustrations: 
<bibRefCitation id="EAB2DDC3B1E947276F5D9A62131DF56A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1973.7.3.265" author="Syed, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Bryology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="265 - 326" refId="B28" refString="Syed, H, 1973. A taxonomic study of Bryum capillare Hedw. and related species. Journal of Bryology 7 (3): 265 - 326, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1973.7.3.265" title="A taxonomic study of Bryum capillare Hedw. and related species." url="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1973.7.3.265" volume="7" year="1973">Syed 1973</bibRefCitation>
